blog.name: dahniwitchoflight
blog.title: Dahni
blog.description:
I am Dahni, an INTP, Witch of Light and Derse Dreamer In The Land of Fog and Reflection. I write a lot about Homestuck's SBURB, God Tier and Land Quest (aka “Classpect”) system and I have a variety of clickable tags/links here about different topics related to it where you can find all my posts about said topics such as Aspect, Class, Derse or Prospit, Class Active/Passive Spectrum, Inversion/Overembracing, Denizens, Land Quests and finally just SBURB, under which falls all of the above plus the other less important parts of SBURB like Cruxite Artifacts, Fraymotifs, Consorts, Strife Specibus, Soul Animals (Like Jade’s Hummingbirds) and other extra specific bits that aren’t major enough to warrant their own tags.

I also tag/link all specific God Tiers in the format of "Class of Aspect" so for example Witch of Light, as well as tagging specific aspects/classes as "Light Aspect" and "Witch Class" And I do this not just for the Witch of Light but for all Aspects and Classes and God Tiers, so if you wanna find all the things I’ve ever talked about in regards to a specific class, aspect or god tier, just search under their tag in my blog.

Finally, the final tag/link that I have is just a collection of every Guide I’ve ever written about various parts of SBURB, like, how to choose a Land/Denizen/God Tier/Consort etc etc anything at all that tries to help you find out what SBURB thing you would have is all under the tag/link called Guides for easy access.

Also I have both a Twitch Account and a Youtube Channel for making and then storing the vids I make when I talk for hours about Homestuck/clearing out my insane huge inbox in a timely manner.

And then finally some extra personal tidbits about me, is that other than Homestuck, I very much enjoy (and oftentimes analyze/theorize/post about) other things that I really like such as Kingdom Hearts, RWBY, Legend of Zelda, Pokemon, Undertale, Steven Universe, Tarot Cards, Name Meanings and Astrology

summary: Is there even a chance that they're going to change this???
question: Is there even a chance that they're going to change this???
answer:
Only one way to find out. 

I did email the pokemon company support, they basically said “not our problem, we dont make the video games nintendo does” saying this:

“Please note, the Pokemon Company International does not publish, develop or support the games developed by Game Freak for Nintendo systems and we are unable to assist with this issue as we do not have the tools or means to do so. Please reach out to Nintendo using the link below.” 

and when I did reach out to nintendo using this link: https://www.nintendo.com/consumer/index.jsp that they sent me

I basically clicked on random shit until I could find a help chat service and requested to give feedback about gamefreak shitting on the pokemon series and the need for them to be removed

the person i chatted with was sympathetic (and real since they made pokemon references with me, so they understand) but unable to do anything except document the feedback into the system

So if anythings gonna get done about Gamefreak and the games, its gonna be through Nintendo, not the Pokemon company

and Nintendo has a good track record so far of caring about the fans and the quality of the games, so go bother Nintendo about it

go document that feedback is all i can say

summary: A dramatization of yesterday’s events of public reaction in an alternate timeline, as I can only guess they would surely play...
caption:
A dramatization of yesterday’s events of public reaction in an alternate timeline, as I can only guess they would surely play out based on the sheer volume and prominence of anti-Minecraft posts in regards to Super Smash Bros. on Know Your Meme, which is actually really annoying, at least in my highly selective perception. The specific KYM user depicted in the bottom-right is one “Artichoke”, whose relevant activity for which I put him in that role will not be linked nor identified here for decent taste’s sake.

In all seriousness in regards to what we actually got instead - and I say this sincerely and without hyperbole - I literally cried tears of joy; there was not a single character I wanted more, although I do feel the reveal cinematic itself could have been much more creative, but that, of course, is a nitpick if ever there was one. Now that Banjo-Kazooie is accounted for, I’d say, based on both my own opinion and the visible public consensus on KYM and similar places, that the “holy grail” status among the most-wanted characters still yet to show up now resides with the Doom guy, and based on the incredibly high standard set by the first three DLC fighters, I’d say the addition thereof seems very much feasible to actually happen at this point, not that I’ll particularly complain if they go with something else, or really almost anything else, as I can’t think of many choices so poor as to actually sour the mood towards the overall game in any significant way now that we have what was probably the single most-wanted addition on a global scale.

On a related note of rambling and as I said in the comment whose heavy downvoting on KYM inspired me in large part to make this image, the Minecraft character, in the event of joining at any future point, should be called “Minecrafter” or “Minecraftsman” instead of “Steve”, in the vein of “Pokémon Trainer” and, as of now, “The Hero”.
